# Enum, Wrapper Class, Autoboxing and Unboxing

Wrapper(boxing) varsa, biri reference digeri primitiv tipli olur, casting sadece tipi deyisdirir eyni aile daxilinde (meselen: int, double, float), parsing muxtelif aile daxilinde (stringden deyisende) istifade olunur.

- `Enum` (Enumeration)

    a special data type in Java that is used to define a group of constant (immutable) values (days of the week). `Enum` provides Type Safety, Readability of the code.

- Create `Enum`

    public enum WeekDay {}. Values are written in uppercase letters separated by commas. Enum values are referenced using a dot (.).

    - Usage of `Enum`

        ![image.png](attachment:5ae4274a-4ad2-488b-99cf-8be20c870000:image.png)

- Methods of `Enum`
    - **`values()`**: Return all values of `Enum` as an array.
    - **`valueOf(String name)`**: Returns the `enum` constant  corresponding to the given `String` name. This method is not there to call enums in code, but to convert strings from external sources to enums.
    - **`ordinal()`**: Returns the order of the constant  within `enum` (index, start from 0).
    - Usage of methods

        ![image.png](attachment:23b2d625-cb16-425d-8799-013442ebddfb:image.png)

- `Wrapper` class

    Special classes that "wrap" primitive data types into objects. Each primitive type has own `Wrapper` class.

    - Example

        ![image.png](attachment:27f04051-1413-48e9-9cc3-bea9481e8b71:image.png)

- Why we need `Wrapper` ?
    1. Java Collection Framework (`ArrayList`, `HashMap` etc.) only works with objects. To store primitive types in these collections, they need to be converted to Wrapper classes.
        - Example

            ![image.png](attachment:67377b74-023b-4f14-bd59-984bb80104d4:image.png)

    2. Primitive types can not take a null value (`int a = null;` will give an error). Since wrapper classes are objects, they can take a null value.
    3. Utility Methods: `Wrapper` classes provide various utility(useful) methods. For instance, the Integer.parseInt("123") method converts a String to an int.
- Autoboxing

    Autoboxing is the automatic conversion of a primitive type into its corresponding Wrapper class. The compiler does this for us behind the scenes.

    - Example

        ![image.png](attachment:c9fbb8e3-7976-4946-8205-1bc0084371a3:image.png)

- Unboxing

    Automatic conversion of a Wrapper class object into the corresponding primitive type.

    - Example

        ![image.png](attachment:fddd3516-13f9-4b53-9e4c-1e31bb9d66cf:image.png)

